
[1]covetousness

   COVETOUSNESS, n.

   1. A strong or inordinate desire of obtaining and possessing some
   supposed good; usually in a bad sense, and applied to an inordinate
   desire of wealth or avarice.

   Out of the heart proceedeth covetousness. Mark 7.

   Mortify your members--and covetousness which is idolatry. Colossians 3.

   2. Strong desire; eagerness.
